description:
Sacrifice of the New by Russell Jackson


A Lovecraftian story of a young woman's empowerment...

A young woman named Jessica, who is haunted by her dim memories of being kidnapped and raped by cultists. The police killed them. But are they really dead? Returning after her rescue to live with her loving, but troubled extended family, Jessie soon begins to discover her own potential, as well as the true nature of the leader of the cult, and the god that they worship... And that he may soon be returning from the dead to make her his bride...

Warning: Contains strong language. Approx. 54,000 words. 


Pdf, epub, and mobi (Kindle) formats.
